                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Conference/242: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-15T20:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 15, 1937—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 15—5:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. The Conference met this afternoon and adopted the declaration textually as
                    telegraphed in my 31, November 13, midnight, with Italy voting against and
                    Norway, Sweden and Denmark despite declarations endorsing the general principles
                    involved abstaining from voting.</p>
                <p>The next session has been called for Monday afternoon, November 22.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
